I'm not generally a fan of VR experiences that aren't games, but the visuals compliment the song incredibly well, and it's great for showing VR off to people who might not have much mobility. The knives are a small bonus, though it'd be nice if they stayed in your hands until you let go instead of just popping out of existence after a certain length of time. In any case, I would love to see more free apps with this style.
Great song, fantastic visuals, fun interactions. So cool to see this from Titmouse, I love their content!

its really cool and a great idea though i wish there was more i could do i love it. the neon lights how stuff moves with you the song itself is good just really cool.

This music video is a psychedelic blast through a neon-laced void. Remember the end of 2001 A Space Odyssey? Imagine cruising through that black hole in a tricked-out convertible with sick EDM beats and scenery to match. Except you don't need to imagine it, because you can download this app and do it. I started out sitting on my butt because I was tired, but this had me on my feet before the music even started, and put a stupid smile on my face in under ten seconds. It's free. It's short. (It's a music video.) It's goddam immersive. (Try headbanging a little.) Just play the goddam music. Goddam son.
And very strange.  Sometimes strange can barely rise to the level of "ho-hum".  This is NOT that kind of strange.  This is far out!
that was a serious head nodding VR experience. you're flying through an animated music video with a demon chick, drawing and grabbing knives as you go. loved every second

I love to put this on after a few and have a dance! 
EPIC!
super amazing experience! and it's free!!! must try!!!

Bad music  and washed out colours. not bad for a free app but needs improvements. starting with some saturation and offer more types of songs or even your own music. didn't finish watching an uninstall coz it grew very tired of it.  it offers no surprises, regardless i understand it was alot of work to make.
Really cool concept. Love the music.

This game is a must have for techno, edm, trap, and dancehall music lovers. I even sugest it if you dont like these types just because the music goes perfectly with the graphics! I have played it so much and it never gets old. An amazing VR experiance and a must have for all oculus owners!

review_title: Sit, Stand, or dance.... great song
one_reviews_text: I've been adding music to my VR library so I can just sit back and enjoy some music while enjoying visual pleasures and sipping wine- which you can totally do with the headset on! The song is catchy and I really like the art. Knives fall all around you which you can interact with. Just know there is a demon chick who appears above, below, and next to you. She is naked but a drawing so.... it's all good right lol! You decide, her picture is right there on the cover so if you don't want to see more of her then don't get this one.

review_title: exactly what I wanted to create
one_reviews_text: When I bought my Oculus Rift nearly 2 years ago I intended on learning how to use Unity to create a Surrealist music video for some of my electronic music. This is the closest I've seen to whay I imagined.
Very neice :)

Don't know how age restriction on this is only 3+ as it has blatant demonic depictions. Nothing much to do besides grabbing virtual knives with your hand and drawing lines with your fingers, while demonic pictures flash around you on the beat of a loud song. At least it is free, but I still want it out of my library.
This is my new standerd for vr eperences the music is great and the art is amazing, and even though i have seen it 20 + times i still love putting it on.

Great concept, great music, a really fun 5 minutes dancing around in VR!

HIghly recommended, the trailer and description don't do this experience justice, it is seriously good and what VR should be like!
Great experience. This is how all future music video should be done, in VR. Wouldn't mind multiple sit throughs just because of the visual awesomeness.

review_title: Sword is easy to grab in standing room
one_reviews_text: Don't listen to the troll review, you can easily grab the sword in standing room only or seated.  But you really want to stand for this one to see all the amazing stuff around you.  This is one of the absolute best music video VR experiences and it's free.  You can grab swords, draw, and grab the stick shift.  There's also some other things I don't want to spoil that you effect.  I loved the music and the visuals were top notch and creative.  We need more of this in VR.

I do a lot of art in VR so I love seeing stuff made with Tiltbrush. This was a cool, short music video, if not a little bit repetetive after a while, could have used a few more assets.

Couple of odd requests: Wish the knife was turned 90 degrees. Seemed like a very strange way to hold it. Also wish the drawings you could make with your hands trailed behind you while the stage was in movement. It was a bit jarring to have them float with me while the stage was in motion.

This was actually a surprise hit for me. It reminded me of the old 80's music videos except you're in the middle of it. All of it ties together well with the song. I hope they come out with more of the same quality.
This is seriously the best in its class. Psychedelic meets cyberpunk meets outstanding music. Absolutely must check this one out!!
Yall creative, keep it that way
Best VR video clip I've seen yet. Pretty swanky song as well.

This was a new experience. I feel pretty often that I've seen most everything, but this blew my mind. An interactive, artistic, VR music video. With that description, I still wasn't prepared for it. I stood there for the first half with the biggest grin on my face. If someone had walked in, I guarantee they would have had some questions. It was like being in some kind of 80's movie drug fueled fever dream. Of all the different non-game experiences in VR that I hope I get more content for, music videos just jumped to the top of the list.

Great experience! Love the visuals and the music. Definitely something I include when demoing the Rift to friends. I do have 2 requests: Remove the need to use Touch to start it. Can we just look at the dagger? I hate wasting the battery. Also, the second round of text has some bad aliasing making it hard to read. Can we have a high quality setting to max the anti aliasing?

One of the things I really like about VR are the "experiences".  Just sit back and watch creativity flow and not always have to do something.  This is one of those that I could certainly watch over and over again and show to my friends and family.  Looking forward to more of these ..... because if anything, they are just plain fun!  Great job devs.
This experience just makes you want to dance through the whole thing. Very trippy. #DMT
This is a videoclip that uses neon like colours and 3D effects. It's very well made and well worth the download. I enjoyed it very much. Thanks!
Probably the best 5 minutes in VR right now. Show it 2 yourself and random people and loved ones.

Just a simple yet really good VR experience.

Great concept, I'm a total metal head but can still enjoy the experience.  Need Metallica to do one next and that would be awesome...

My favourite of the VR music videos so far is Fantasynth, but this comes a close second for something completely different and a cracking song too! A must try for everyone really, you won't regret it! :)
Talk about a trip going on here.. Can be enjoyed sober, drunk or on substances! Awesome! :)
wow... just wish there was binaural sound to match it, would increase immersion of these 3d music vids :)
Great experience.
Dark, trippy, rockin' ride through a neon-colored twitching fantasy.  I thoroughly enjoyed it, and played it a few times in a row.
It has a sign to grab something just beyond your reach.  Can't reset position or move beyond the guardian to grab it. Cant use a button, keyboard, or controller to start scene.
It took a bit to use the new control panel to resest my position, but this is amazing. No lag whatsoever, stunning graphics and you can get your rave on. 10/10 Would play again!
I want more of this, a lot more. Such a crazy experience.
How cool, what a fun, psychedelic and unique ride.
